POLOKWANE – Voting at the ANC Limpopo’s 10th elective conference has resulted in Chupu Mathabatha’s re-election as chairperson. The conference, which is underway at the Ranch Resort has been described as a “peaceful” conference by the ANC’s acting treasurer Paul Mashatile, who commended the province for hosting a “well handled” conference. Read more: 1 200 ANC delegates converge to elect new Limpopo leadership Mathabatha contested against Public Works, Roads and Infrastructure MEC Dr Dickson Masemola for the position of chairperson and won with 781 votes to 389. The newly elected Top 5 in the province includes: Chairperson- Chupu Mathabatha Deputy Chairperson – Florence Radzilani Secretary – Reuben Madadzhe Deputy secretary – Basikopo Makamu Treasurer – Nakedi Sibanda Kekana Mathabatha committed to discussing service delivery with delegates and said he hopes the commissions which will take place during the conference will thoroughly discuss ways to sort service delivery needs of the province. Re-elected chairperson of the ANC in Limpopo, Chupu Mathabatha speaks on the Top 5's election and dealing with corruption accordingly #ANCLimpopo pic.twitter.com/lX4elFdG23 — Polokwane Review (@PolokwaneReview) June 4, 2022  He added that the ANC is allergic to corruption and that the party does not want to be associated with it. “Those individuals found to be corrupt within the ANC will be dealt with accordingly,” he said. 